@startuml sequence-github
title MONSITE — Connexion via GitHub (OAuth2 + PKCE)

autonumber

actor "Utilisateur" as User
participant "Navigateur" as Browser
participant "MONSITE\n(Client App)" as Monsite
participant "GitHub\n(Authorization Server)" as GitHubAuth
participant "GitHub\n(Resource Server)" as GitHubRes

User -> Browser: Clique "Se connecter avec GitHub"
Browser -> Monsite: GET /api/auth/github/authorize
activate Monsite
Monsite -> Monsite: Génère state (CSRF) + PKCE\n(code_verifier, code_challenge = SHA256(verifier))
Monsite -> Browser: 302 Redirect vers GitHub\n+ Set-Cookie monsite_oauth_state\n(signé HMAC, HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax, TTL 10 min)
deactivate Monsite

Browser -> GitHubAuth: GET /login/oauth/authorize\n?client_id&redirect_uri&response_type=code\n&scope=read:user user:email\n&state&code_challenge&code_challenge_method=S256
activate GitHubAuth
GitHubAuth -> User: Affiche l'écran de connexion / consentement GitHub
User -> GitHubAuth: S'authentifie et autorise MONSITE
GitHubAuth -> Browser: 302 Redirect\n/api/auth/github/callback?code&state
deactivate GitHubAuth

Browser -> Monsite: GET /api/auth/github/callback?code&state
activate Monsite
Monsite -> Monsite: Vérifie signature + expiration du cookie state\ncompare state (timingSafeEqual)\nsupprime immédiatement monsite_oauth_state
Monsite -> GitHubAuth: POST /login/oauth/access_token\n(client_id, client_secret, code, redirect_uri,\ngrant_type=authorization_code, code_verifier)\nHeaders: Accept: application/json, User-Agent
activate GitHubAuth
GitHubAuth -> Monsite: 200 { access_token }\n(JSON grâce à Accept: application/json —\nGitHub répondrait en x-www-form-urlencoded sinon)
deactivate GitHubAuth

Monsite -> GitHubRes: GET /user\nAuthorization: Bearer access_token\nUser-Agent: monsite-oauth-client
activate GitHubRes
GitHubRes -> Monsite: 200 { id, login, name, email, avatar_url }\n(email peut être null si privé)
deactivate GitHubRes

Monsite -> Monsite: Construit le profil {provider: "github",\nproviderAccountId: String(id), email,\nname: name ?? login, avatarUrl: avatar_url}\ncrée le cookie de session monsite_session
Monsite -> Browser: 307 Redirect /profile\n+ Set-Cookie monsite_session\n(signé HMAC, HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax, TTL 2h)
deactivate Monsite

Browser -> Monsite: GET /profile (cookie monsite_session)
Monsite -> Browser: 200 Page de profil (nom, courriel, avatar)

note over Monsite, GitHubAuth
  GitHub n'implémente pas OpenID Connect (pas de id_token JWT,
  contrairement à Google) : le profil vient d'un appel REST classique
  à /user avec le jeton d'accès. C'est le même client OAuth générique
  (buildAuthorizationUrl / exchangeCodeForToken / fetchUserInfo) qui
  gère ce cas, uniquement paramétré différemment (endpoints, scope,
  mapUserInfo) — illustre l'avertissement du PDF sur l'incompatibilité
  potentielle des choix entre fournisseurs.
end note

@enduml
